ABUJA â€“ Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu APC frontline presidential aspirant has paid a condolence visit on the Government and People Owo over last Sunday attack on St Francis Catholic Church that claim the lives of over 30 people. Speaking when he called on Ondo State Governor Rotimi Akeredolu, the All Progressives Congress National Leader promised to work with the governor to bring succour to the victims of Owo Massacre. Speaking at the Palace of Olowo, Oba Ajibade Gbadegesin Ogunoye, during condolence visit in company of Arakunrin Akeredolu, Tinubu condemned the violent attack on innocent worshippers and described the attack as evil that must be defeated saying there is no place for such hatred and wanton taking of innocent lives in our country. -Advertisement- He noted that the South West had never witnessed an attack of such magnitude saying it was horrendous. Asiwaju Tinubu seized the opportunity to call on both Federal and the state governments to work together to strengthen security around the country. Before he visited the church for on the spot assessment, Asiwaju Tinubu pledged the sum of N50million to the victims and another N25million to the Owo Catholic Church. Governor Akeredolu who appreciated Tinubu for pausing his presidential campaign activities less than 24 hours to the APC convention promised to either bring the assailants down to the state for justice or take justice to them. On the trip to Owo with Tinubu were former Speaker of House of Representatives, Yakubu Dogara, Chairman of TETFUND, Kashim Ibrahim-Imam, former APC National Vice Chairman, Southwest, Chief Pius Akinyelure, former Chairman of Economic and Financial Crime Commission, Nuhu Ribadu and former Deputy Governor of Lagos State, Otunba Femi Pedro. Recall that Gunmen invaded St. Francis Catholic Church in Owo on Sunday and massacred over 30 people who were mostly children and women.